					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/dr-wartheim" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(999012); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=999012&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610182973" alt="Dr Wartheim" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=999012)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/dr-wartheim" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(999012); return false;" >Dr Wartheim</a></span> <span class="odate time_1332544151 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">23 Mar 2012 23:09</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-1401030">
									

<p>I might be jumping to conclusions a bit but&#8230; To me this seems like a Neon Genesis Evangelion expy for the following reasons:<br />
SCP originates from a &quot;class 2 impact&quot; = the Second Impact.<br />
&quot;seven organs tentatively identified as eyes&quot; = the 7-eyed Lilith.<br />
Jewish mysticism galore!</p>
<p>Furthermore, the tone in which the SCP is written is not up to standard in my opinion. Overuse of &quot;##-class&quot; (&quot;11-class munitions&quot;, etc.) as well as unscientific phrases such as &quot;a melodious voice&quot; and that bit about extra-dimensional beings doesn't fit with the cold, clinical, analytical tone of an SCP page.</p>
<p>And the worst offense, in my eyes, is that this SCP is just plain bland. There is nothing new or clever or interesting or frightening about it. There's no &quot;hook&quot;. There's nothing that lingers in the mind of the reader, nothing to set it apart from &quot;generic pseudo-kabalistic doomsday&quot;. The other points I raised may be forgivable, this one isn't.</p>

							</div>

								
					
